113static enum ld_plugin_status
114message (int level ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
115 const char * format, ...)
116{
117 va_list args;
118 va_start (args, format);
119 printf ("bfd plugin: ");
120 vprintf (format, args);
121 putchar ('\n');
122 va_end (args);
123 return LDPS_OK;
124}
125
126/* Register a claim-file handler. */
127static ld_plugin_claim_file_handler claim_file;
128
129static enum ld_plugin_status
130register_claim_file (ld_plugin_claim_file_handler handler)
131{
132 claim_file = handler;
133 return LDPS_OK;
134}
135
136static enum ld_plugin_status
137add_symbols (void * handle,
138 int nsyms,
139 const struct ld_plugin_symbol * syms)
140{
141 bfd *abfd = handle;
142 struct plugin_data_struct *plugin_data =
143 bfd_alloc (abfd, sizeof (plugin_data_struct));
144
145 plugin_data->nsyms = nsyms;
146 plugin_data->syms = syms;
147
148 if (nsyms != 0)
149 abfd->flags |= HAS_SYMS;
150
151 abfd->tdata.plugin_data = plugin_data;
152 return LDPS_OK;
153}

163int
164bfd_plugin_open_input (bfd *ibfd, struct ld_plugin_input_file *file)
165{
166 bfd *iobfd;
167
168 iobfd = ibfd;
169 while (iobfd->my_archive
170 && !bfd_is_thin_archive (iobfd->my_archive))
171 iobfd = iobfd->my_archive;
172 file->name = iobfd->filename;
173
174 if (!iobfd->iostream && !bfd_open_file (iobfd))
175 return 0;
176
177 /* The plugin API expects that the file descriptor won't be closed
178 and reused as done by the bfd file cache. So open it again.
179 dup isn't good enough. plugin IO uses lseek/read while BFD uses
180 fseek/fread. It isn't wise to mix the unistd and stdio calls on
181 the same underlying file descriptor. */
182 file->fd = open (file->name, O_RDONLY | O_BINARY);
183 if (file->fd < 0)
184 return 0;
185
186 if (iobfd == ibfd)
187 {
188 struct stat stat_buf;
189 if (fstat (file->fd, &stat_buf))
190 return 0;
191 file->offset = 0;
192 file->filesize = stat_buf.st_size;
193 }
194 else
195 {
196 file->offset = ibfd->origin;
197 file->filesize = arelt_size (ibfd);
198 }
199 return 1;
200}
201
202static int
203try_claim (bfd *abfd)
204{
205 int claimed = 0;
206 struct ld_plugin_input_file file;
207
208 file.handle = abfd;
209 if (!bfd_plugin_open_input (abfd, &file))
210 return 0;
211 claim_file (&file, &claimed);
212 if (!claimed)
213 close (file.fd);
214 return claimed;
215}
216
217static int
218try_load_plugin (const char *pname, bfd *abfd, int *has_plugin_p)
219{
220 void *plugin_handle;
221 struct ld_plugin_tv tv[4];
222 int i;
223 ld_plugin_onload onload;
224 enum ld_plugin_status status;
225
226 *has_plugin_p = 0;
227
228 plugin_handle = dlopen (pname, RTLD_NOW);
229 if (!plugin_handle)
230 {
231 _bfd_error_handler ("%s\n", dlerror ());
232 return 0;
233 }
234
235 onload = dlsym (plugin_handle, "onload");
236 if (!onload)
237 goto err;
238
239 i = 0;
240 tv[i].tv_tag = LDPT_MESSAGE;
241 tv[i].tv_u.tv_message = message;
242
243 ++i;
244 tv[i].tv_tag = LDPT_REGISTER_CLAIM_FILE_HOOK;
245 tv[i].tv_u.tv_register_claim_file = register_claim_file;
246
247 ++i;
248 tv[i].tv_tag = LDPT_ADD_SYMBOLS;
249 tv[i].tv_u.tv_add_symbols = add_symbols;
250
251 ++i;
252 tv[i].tv_tag = LDPT_NULL;
253 tv[i].tv_u.tv_val = 0;
254
255 status = (*onload)(tv);
256
257 if (status != LDPS_OK)
258 goto err;
259
260 *has_plugin_p = 1;
261
262 abfd->plugin_format = bfd_plugin_no;
263
264 if (!claim_file)
265 goto err;
266
267 if (!try_claim (abfd))
268 goto err;
269
270 abfd->plugin_format = bfd_plugin_yes;
271
272 return 1;
273
274 err:
275 return 0;
276}

329static int
330load_plugin (bfd *abfd)
331{
332 char *plugin_dir;
333 char *p;
334 DIR *d;
335 struct dirent *ent;
336 int found = 0;
337
338 if (!has_plugin)
339 return found;
340
341 if (plugin_name)
342 return try_load_plugin (plugin_name, abfd, &has_plugin);
343
344 if (plugin_program_name == NULL)
345 return found;
346
347 plugin_dir = concat (BINDIR, "/../lib/bfd-plugins", NULL);
348 p = make_relative_prefix (plugin_program_name,
349 BINDIR,
350 plugin_dir);
351 free (plugin_dir);
352 plugin_dir = NULL;
353
354 d = opendir (p);
355 if (!d)
356 goto out;
357
358 while ((ent = readdir (d)))
359 {
360 char *full_name;
361 struct stat s;
362 int valid_plugin;
363
364 full_name = concat (p, "/", ent->d_name, NULL);
365 if (stat(full_name, &s) == 0 && S_ISREG (s.st_mode))
366 found = try_load_plugin (full_name, abfd, &valid_plugin);
367 if (has_plugin <= 0)
368 has_plugin = valid_plugin;
369 free (full_name);
370 if (found)
371 break;
372 }
373
374 out:
375 free (p);
376 if (d)
377 closedir (d);
378
379 return found;
380}

383static const bfd_target *
384bfd_plugin_object_p (bfd *abfd)
385{
386 if (ld_plugin_object_p)
387 return ld_plugin_object_p (abfd);
388
389 if (abfd->plugin_format == bfd_plugin_unknown && !load_plugin (abfd))
390 return NULL;
391
392 return abfd->plugin_format == bfd_plugin_yes ? abfd->xvec : NULL;
393}

460static long
461bfd_plugin_get_symtab_upper_bound (bfd *abfd)
462{
463 struct plugin_data_struct *plugin_data = abfd->tdata.plugin_data;
464 long nsyms = plugin_data->nsyms;
465
466 BFD_ASSERT (nsyms >= 0);
467
468 return ((nsyms + 1) * sizeof (asymbol *));
469}

471static flagword
472convert_flags (const struct ld_plugin_symbol *sym)
473{
474 switch (sym->def)
475 {
476 case LDPK_DEF:
477 case LDPK_COMMON:
478 case LDPK_UNDEF:
479 return BSF_GLOBAL;
480
481 case LDPK_WEAKUNDEF:
482 case LDPK_WEAKDEF:
483 return BSF_GLOBAL | BSF_WEAK;
484
485 default:
486 BFD_ASSERT (0);
487 return 0;
488 }
489}
490
491static long
492bfd_plugin_canonicalize_symtab (bfd *abfd,
493 asymbol **alocation)
494{
495 struct plugin_data_struct *plugin_data = abfd->tdata.plugin_data;
496 long nsyms = plugin_data->nsyms;
497 const struct ld_plugin_symbol *syms = plugin_data->syms;
498 static asection fake_section;
499 static asection fake_common_section;
500 int i;
501
502 fake_section.name = ".text";
503 fake_common_section.flags = SEC_IS_COMMON;
504
505 for (i = 0; i < nsyms; i++)
506 {
507 asymbol *s = bfd_alloc (abfd, sizeof (asymbol));
508
509 BFD_ASSERT (s);
510 alocation[i] = s;
511
512 s->the_bfd = abfd;
513 s->name = syms[i].name;
514 s->value = 0;
515 s->flags = convert_flags (&syms[i]);
516 switch (syms[i].def)
517 {
518 case LDPK_COMMON:
519 s->section = &fake_common_section;
520 break;
521 case LDPK_UNDEF:
522 case LDPK_WEAKUNDEF:
523 s->section = bfd_und_section_ptr;
524 break;
525 case LDPK_DEF:
526 case LDPK_WEAKDEF:
527 s->section = &fake_section;
528 break;
529 default:
530 BFD_ASSERT (0);
531 }
532
533 s->udata.p = (void *) &syms[i];
534 }
535
536 return nsyms;
537}

556/* Make an empty symbol. */
557
558static asymbol *
559bfd_plugin_make_empty_symbol (bfd *abfd)
560{
561 asymbol *new_symbol = bfd_zalloc (abfd, sizeof (asymbol));
562 if (new_symbol == NULL)
563 return new_symbol;
564 new_symbol->the_bfd = abfd;
565 return new_symbol;
566}
